# Cloudflare Pages redirects
# https://developers.cloudflare.com/pages/configuration/redirects/

# --- Legacy .html URLs → clean /path form ---------------------------------
# A handful of pages used to live at /<page>.html. We now serve them at /<page>
# (canonical, hreflang, sitemap all point at the bare path), but external
# inbound links from blogs and older bookmarks may still request the .html
# variant. These 301s send that traffic to the canonical URL with the
# non-www host. List each leaf explicitly so we never accidentally swallow
# an asset request that happens to end in .html.

/about.html         https://socialeraser.app/about          301
/privacy.html       https://socialeraser.app/privacy        301
/terms.html         https://socialeraser.app/terms          301
/support.html       https://socialeraser.app/support        301
/help.html          https://socialeraser.app/help           301
/success.html       https://socialeraser.app/success        301
/guides/twitter.html   https://socialeraser.app/guides/twitter   301
/guides/tiktok.html    https://socialeraser.app/guides/tiktok    301
/guides/youtube.html   https://socialeraser.app/guides/youtube   301
/guides/instagram.html https://socialeraser.app/guides/instagram 301
/guides/facebook.html  https://socialeraser.app/guides/facebook  301

# --- 404 handler -----------------------------------------------------------
# Cloudflare Pages serves 404.html automatically when a path is not found,
# but explicit /404 mapping makes intent clear and protects against future
# static-asset shadowing.
